---
name: jira-ralph
description: TDD implementation loop for Jira subtasks. Fetches ready-for-agent subtasks from a parent story, writes failing tests first, commits, writes implementation, commits, updates Jira status and comments at each stage, creates a draft PR at the end. Invoke with /jira-ralph <PARENT-STORY-KEY> [--mode single|all]
---

# Jira Ralph — TDD Implementation Loop

## Invocation

```
/jira-ralph {{JIRA_PROJECT}}-123 --mode single    # process one subtask, then stop
/jira-ralph {{JIRA_PROJECT}}-123 --mode all       # process all ready-for-agent subtasks
```

Default mode is `single` if `--mode` is omitted.

## Jira Configuration
- Domain: `{{JIRA_DOMAIN}}`
- Project: `{{JIRA_PROJECT}}`
- Pick filter: label = `ready-for-agent` AND status = `To Do`
- Status transitions: `To Do` → `In Progress` → `Done`
- On failure: add label `blocked`, comment reason, halt

## Step 1: Parse Arguments

Extract:
- `PARENT_KEY` — the parent story key (e.g. `{{JIRA_PROJECT}}-123`)
- `MODE` — `single` or `all` (default: `single`)

If PARENT_KEY is missing, stop and tell the user:
> "Usage: /jira-ralph {{JIRA_PROJECT}}-123 [--mode single|all]"

## Step 2: Fetch Parent Story

```
mcp__plugin_atlassian_atlassian__getJiraIssue(
  cloudId: "{{JIRA_DOMAIN}}",
  issueIdOrKey: "<PARENT_KEY>"
)
```

Extract: parent summary. Build branch slug from summary (lowercase, hyphens, max 40 chars).

Branch name: `feat/<PARENT_KEY>-<slug>` (e.g. `feat/{{JIRA_PROJECT}}-123-user-auth-otp`)

## Step 3: Fetch Ready Subtasks

```
mcp__plugin_atlassian_atlassian__searchJiraIssuesUsingJql(
  cloudId: "{{JIRA_DOMAIN}}",
  jql: "project = {{JIRA_PROJECT}} AND parent = <PARENT_KEY> AND labels = ready-for-agent AND status = \"To Do\" ORDER BY created ASC",
  fields: ["summary", "description", "status", "labels", "key"]
)
```

If no subtasks found, stop:
> "No ready-for-agent subtasks with status 'To Do' found under <PARENT_KEY>. Label subtasks with 'ready-for-agent' and ensure status is 'To Do'."

If MODE = `single`: take only the first subtask.
If MODE = `all`: take all subtasks in order.

## Step 4: Prepare Git Branch

Check if branch already exists:
```bash
git fetch origin
git branch -a | grep "feat/<PARENT_KEY>-<slug>"
```

If branch does not exist:
```bash
git checkout develop
git pull origin develop
git checkout -b feat/<PARENT_KEY>-<slug>
```

If branch exists:
```bash
git checkout feat/<PARENT_KEY>-<slug>
git pull origin feat/<PARENT_KEY>-<slug> 2>/dev/null || true
```

## Step 5: Process Each Subtask

Repeat this block for each subtask. Track `SUBTASK_ITERATION` counter (starts at 1, max 5).

---

### 5a. Transition to In Progress

```
mcp__plugin_atlassian_atlassian__transitionJiraIssue(
  cloudId: "{{JIRA_DOMAIN}}",
  issueIdOrKey: "<SUBTASK_KEY>",
  transition: "In Progress"
)
```

### 5b. Comment: Picked Up

```
mcp__plugin_atlassian_atlassian__addCommentToJiraIssue(
  cloudId: "{{JIRA_DOMAIN}}",
  issueIdOrKey: "<SUBTASK_KEY>",
  body: "🔄 Picked up by agent. Writing failing tests now.\nBranch: feat/<PARENT_KEY>-<slug>"
)
```

### 5c. Write Failing Tests

Read the subtask description and acceptance criteria thoroughly. Also read the **parent story** (`PARENT_KEY`) description and acceptance criteria.

**Extract PO-written test cases:**
- Scan both the subtask and parent story for any test cases, scenarios, or acceptance criteria the PO has explicitly listed (numbered lists, "Given/When/Then", "should…" bullets, test scenario tables, etc.).
- If PO test cases exist: you MUST cover ALL of them. Write a test for each one by name. Then add any additional cases you identify (edge cases, failure paths, PRD rules, security constraints) on top.
- If no PO test cases exist: derive the full test set yourself from the subtask + parent story + PRD.

Write test file(s) following project conventions:
- Co-locate `*.spec.ts` next to source files
- Use `Test.createTestingModule` with mocked dependencies (unit tests)
- Do NOT write implementation code yet — tests must fail at this point

**Self-verify before committing:** After writing, scan your test file and cross-check every PO-listed case by name. If any are missing, add them before proceeding.

Run tests to confirm they fail:
```bash
pnpm test --testPathPattern="<test-file-name>" 2>&1 | tail -20
```

Expected: tests fail (not compile errors — tests should compile and run but assertions fail).

If tests have compile errors, fix type errors and re-run. This does NOT count as an iteration.

### 5d. Commit Failing Tests

```bash
git add <test-files>
git commit -m "test: write failing tests for <SUBTASK_KEY> - <subtask summary short>"
```

### 5e. Comment: Tests Committed

```
mcp__plugin_atlassian_atlassian__addCommentToJiraIssue(
  cloudId: "{{JIRA_DOMAIN}}",
  issueIdOrKey: "<SUBTASK_KEY>",
  body: "✅ Failing tests committed. PO-listed cases covered: {list PO cases by name, or 'none specified — test set derived from acceptance criteria'}. Now implementing."
)
```

### 5f. Write Implementation

Read the subtask description, acceptance criteria, and the failing tests.

Implement minimal code to make all tests pass. Follow project conventions (CLAUDE.md):
- No Prisma in controllers
- Use repository pattern for data access
- Throw NestJS HTTP exceptions at service layer
- No `any`, no `console.log`, no silent failures

After writing implementation, run tests:
```bash
pnpm test --testPathPattern="<test-file-name>" 2>&1 | tail -30
```

### 5g. Retry Loop (max 5 iterations)

If tests fail:
- Increment `SUBTASK_ITERATION`
- If `SUBTASK_ITERATION` > 5: go to **Step 5h (Halt)**
- Read the failure output carefully
- Fix the implementation (do NOT change the tests)
- Run tests again
- Repeat

If tests pass: go to **Step 5i**.

### 5h. Halt on Failure

If 5 iterations exhausted and tests still fail:

Add label `blocked`:
```
mcp__plugin_atlassian_atlassian__updateJiraIssue(
  cloudId: "{{JIRA_DOMAIN}}",
  issueIdOrKey: "<SUBTASK_KEY>",
  labels: ["ready-for-agent", "blocked"]
)
```

Comment with failure details:
```
mcp__plugin_atlassian_atlassian__addCommentToJiraIssue(
  cloudId: "{{JIRA_DOMAIN}}",
  issueIdOrKey: "<SUBTASK_KEY>",
  body: "🚫 Agent halted after 5 iterations. Tests still failing.\n\nLast failure output:\n{paste last test output}\n\nManual review required."
)
```

Transition back to `To Do`:
```
mcp__plugin_atlassian_atlassian__transitionJiraIssue(
  cloudId: "{{JIRA_DOMAIN}}",
  issueIdOrKey: "<SUBTASK_KEY>",
  transition: "To Do"
)
```

Stop the entire batch. Do NOT proceed to the next subtask.

Tell the user:
> "Halted on <SUBTASK_KEY>. Tests did not pass after 5 iterations. Subtask marked blocked. Inspect the test output above and fix manually."

### 5i. Commit Implementation

```bash
git add <implementation-files>
git commit -m "feat: implement <SUBTASK_KEY> - <subtask summary short>"
```

### 5j. Run Full Test Suite

```bash
pnpm test 2>&1 | tail -20
```

If any previously-passing tests now fail (regression), fix them before proceeding. Do not count regression fixes against the 5-iteration cap.

### 5k. Transition to Done

```
mcp__plugin_atlassian_atlassian__transitionJiraIssue(
  cloudId: "{{JIRA_DOMAIN}}",
  issueIdOrKey: "<SUBTASK_KEY>",
  transition: "Done"
)
```

### 5l. Comment: Complete

```
mcp__plugin_atlassian_atlassian__addCommentToJiraIssue(
  cloudId: "{{JIRA_DOMAIN}}",
  issueIdOrKey: "<SUBTASK_KEY>",
  body: "✅ Implementation complete. Tests passing.\nCommits:\n- test: write failing tests for <SUBTASK_KEY>\n- feat: implement <SUBTASK_KEY>"
)
```

---

Repeat Step 5 for the next subtask (if MODE = `all`).

## Step 6: Push Branch

```bash
git push -u origin feat/<PARENT_KEY>-<slug>
```

## Step 7: Create Draft PR

```bash
gh pr create \
  --title "<PARENT_KEY>: <parent story summary>" \
  --body "$(cat <<'EOF'
## Jira Story
https://{{JIRA_DOMAIN}}/browse/<PARENT_KEY>

## Subtasks completed
<list each SUBTASK_KEY with link and one-line summary>

## Test plan
- All unit tests pass: pnpm test
- Each acceptance criterion covered by a spec file
- No regressions in full test suite

## Notes
Draft PR — review and promote to ready when satisfied.

🤖 Implemented via jira-ralph TDD loop
EOF
)" \
  --base develop \
  --draft
```

Output the PR URL to the user.

## Step 8: Done

Tell the user:
> "✅ Done. Processed N subtask(s) under <PARENT_KEY>. Draft PR: <url>. Review and promote when ready."
